            <scopecontent>
                <p>This is a collection of business records of P. Gramigna &amp; Sons. Materials
                    include: ledgers of receipts and expenses, accounts receivable, checks; journals
                    of income taxes, journals of daily provisions and sea stock, and payroll books.
                    Papers in the collection include: bills for ships provisioned (1924-1929);
                    correspondence; receipts and bills, 1920s-1930s; bills of lading; blank
                    letterhead and bill heads; and ink blotter advertisements for P. Gramigna &amp;
                    Sons. Provisions include food supplies, batteries, paint and paint brushes, nuts
                    and bolts, and matches.</p>
            </scopecontent>

